cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CE, cs.SE 

The paper discusses interconnected dynamic systems and their simplified representations, which are commonly studied in the field of control systems (cs.SY). The use of linear systems as a vehicle for comparison suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG), while the analysis of partial structure representations may also relate to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The discussion of system input-output behavior and model reduction could also be relevant to computer engineering (cs.CE) and software engineering (cs.SE).
